Date: Fri, 14 Jul 2017 11:34:36 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Make timesyncd a "simple" service

the daemon ends up waiting 100 msec on networking conditions before notifying
that it is done, even though that's really not relevant
---
 units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff -Naur systemd-244.20191203/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in systemd-244.20191203.tpg/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in
--- systemd-244.20191203/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in	2019-11-29 16:32:36.000000000 +0000
+++ systemd-244.20191203.tpg/units/systemd-timesyncd.service.in	2019-12-03 12:20:16.346023149 +0000
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@
 SystemCallArchitectures=native
 SystemCallErrorNumber=EPERM
 SystemCallFilter=@system-service @clock
-Type=notify
+Type=simple
 User=systemd-timesync
 @SERVICE_WATCHDOG@
 
